<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/316: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-24T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 24,
                                        1927—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>10. Your No. 25, June 23, 7 p.m. The action which you suggest taking is
                            in accord with your instructions. I approve your supporting adoption of
                            decision by Conference along lines set forth.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>